            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_199653124:af9c0dafeeef",
            "label": "Please provide a brief program description:",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD) manages a diverse portfolio of robotic exploration missions to understand the Earth, the Sun, our solar system, and the universe beyond.\n* SMD's work is guided by the National Academies' Decadal Surveys, which represent the peer-reviewed consensus of the scientific community on the most critical questions facing humanity.\n* The directorate supports high-stakes research and development that drives American innovation in fields ranging from climate monitoring to planetary defense.\n* This $9 billion request restores stability to the SMD portfolio following recent budget volatility, ensuring the U.S. remains the global leader in space-based scientific discovery.",
            "rationale": "Description based on SMD's core mission and the $9B funding ask specified in the reference values.",
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "header": "General Information",
        "description": null,
        "fields": [
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_188932963:bc9533c368d1",
            "label": "How does this request benefit the district? *Please limit to 2,000 characters.",
            "help_text": "Please limit to 2,000 characters.",
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science has invested over $1.25 million across CA-14 institutions and businesses between FY2023 and FY2025, supporting a high-tech local workforce.\n* Funding supports specialized local entities such as Vector Atomic Inc in Pleasanton, which has received over $699,000 in contracts for advanced quantum technology and gravity sensors.\n* Local academic contributions include the California State University, East Bay Foundation, which is leading a $140,726 project to validate carbon transfers for environmental accounting.\n* These investments strengthen the district's STEM talent pipeline and support the regional aerospace economy through partners like Yield Engineering Systems and Spatial Informatics Group.",
            "rationale": "Cited specific local spending totals ($1.25M), and identified top recipients (Vector Atomic, CSU East Bay, Yield Engineering Systems) from the provided CA-14 NASA spending context.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_783720922:37aa38c9b9e8",
            "label": "Describe the problem or issue to be addressed through this request. *Please limit to 2,000 characters.",
            "help_text": "Please limit to 2,000 characters.",
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Recent budget volatility, including a drastic proposed cut to $3.9 billion in FY2026, has created workforce instability and threatened decades of investment in space science.\n* Significant layoffs and the loss of over 4,000 civil servants have eroded critical technical capabilities that are difficult and costly to recover.\n* China is aggressively expanding its space science program, including sample returns from the Moon's far side, challenging U.S. preeminence in setting exploration norms.\n* Insufficient funding threatens the execution of Decadal Survey priorities, which are essential for maintaining the U.S. competitive edge in science and technology.",
            "rationale": "Based on the advocacy talking points regarding budget volatility, workforce losses, and international competition with China.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_635351568:240b32501d1d",
            "label": "Describe the project or program, what it will do, and why it is necessary. *Please limit to 2,000 characters.",
            "help_text": "Please limit to 2,000 characters.",
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* This $9 billion request funds the Science Mission Directorate to execute peer-reviewed exploration roadmaps that secure American leadership in the new space race.\n* The program supports the development of cutting-edge instrumentation and robotic missions that return three dollars to the U.S. economy for every dollar invested.\n* It is necessary to provide the budgetary certainty required for multi-year missions, preventing the project cancellations and workforce flight seen in previous fiscal cycles.\n* Sustained investment ensures the U.S. continues to attract the world's best STEM talent and leads global efforts in planetary defense and climate observation.",
            "rationale": "Combines the $9B funding ask with advocacy points on economic ROI (3:1), workforce stability, and the necessity of decadal priorities.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1384091534:a5e4097cc229",
            "label": "Please include all such partners with whom you will be working or from whom you have requested additional funding for your program or project:",
